Today the Lord turned me to Himself the Author and Perfecter of my faith. Amen, it is not that I have to do but that I must trust the Lord. He Himself in substance as the Spirit in my spirit is my faith. He is God's gift to me and I ask Him and He gives to me the water of life that I may never thirst again nor drink from the world ever again. But simply to take Him as my allotted portion in everything. He Himself bodily is my faith in God. In Him I am saved never to be lost again. In Him I have God. Amen. Jesus Christ is Lord, Amen. He is everything, Amen, and everything is in Him. Amen. 

Once I hoped in Jesus,
 Now I know He's mine;
Once my lamps were dying,
 Now they brightly shine;
Once for death I waited,
 Now His coming hail;
And my hopes are anchored
 Safe within the veil.
